			<div class="content" id="post-content-2665464">
									

<p>Solo and Communism Will Win, would having the dialogue at the end be more vague change your opinion of it? We debated making it more subtle, but weren't sure if it would be <em>too subtle</em> if we didn't include some of the dialogue. However, I see your point.</p>
<p>CWW, to <em>answer</em> part of your inquiry:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Spoilers?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>It is vaguely hinted at, and we wanted it that way so the reader could come to their own conclusions about it, but the pattern screamers knowledge of both Site-83 and English comes from the D-Class that were cycled through it. Hence why the booth rejects being empty now or having non-humans in it, and the <em>There is so much to do</em> bits. From the knowledge they've gathered, one could think that the pattern screamers think that all of humanity has the same ideals as the few D-Class they've encountered up until that point. Whether or not they're trying to be helpful or not is open to interpretation.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Thank you for the honest feedback.</p>

